  "local_port": 40578,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm a US citizen and my boyfriend is Argentinean; if we get married in the US, how long will it take for him to be qualified to work in the US?",
  "response": "If you and your Argentinean boyfriend get married in the U.S., he can become eligible to work in the U.S. by applying for a **marriage-based green card (permanent residency)**. Here\u2019s an overview of the process and timeline:\n\n### Step 1: File the Petition (Form I-130)\n- As the U.S. citizen spouse, you\u2019ll need to file **Form I-130 (Petition for Alien Relative)** with U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS). This establishes your spousal relationship.\n- Processing times for Form I-130 vary but typically take **7\u201315 months**, depending on the USCIS service center handling your case.\n\n### Step 2: Apply for Adjustment of Status (Form I-485)\n- If your spouse is already in the U.S. legally (e.g., on a valid visa), he can file **Form I-485 (Application to Adjust Status)** concurrently with Form I-130 or after the I-130 is approved. This allows him to apply for a green card without leaving the U.S.\n- If he is outside the U.S., he will go through consular processing at a U.S. embassy or consulate in Argentina.\n\n### Step 3: Work Authorization (Form I-765)\n- When filing Form I-485, he can also submit **Form I-765 (Application for Employment Authorization)** to receive an **Employment Authorization Document (EAD)**, which will allow him to work while his green card application is pending.\n- EAD processing typically takes **3\u20137 months** after filing. Once he receives the EAD, he can legally work in the U.S.\n\n### Step 4: Green Card Approval\n- The green card application (Form I-485) typically takes **8\u201314 months** to process. Once approved, he will become a lawful permanent resident (green card holder) and can work indefinitely.\n\n### Summary Timeline\n- **Work Authorization (EAD):** ~3\u20137 months after filing Form I-765 (if filed with Form I-485).\n- **Green Card Approval:** ~8\u201314 months from filing Form I-485.\n\n### Tips:\n1. **File Consistently and Accurately:** Ensure all forms are completed correctly and submitted with the required supporting documents to avoid delays.\n2. **Expedite Requests:** In some cases, you can request expedited processing for the EAD if you can demonstrate financial hardship.\n3. **Consult an Immigration Attorney:** An attorney can help navigate the process and address any complications.\n\nOnce your spouse receives his EAD or green card, he will be legally authorized to work in the U.S.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
